// response_format_json.script
// Generates the structured-output format instruction injected into every main-model request.
//
// Variables available from app_vars (set by settings_controller):
//   GRAPH_EXTRACTION_ENABLED (bool) — whether knowledge-graph entity extraction is active
//
// Python caller is responsible for replacing the {TOOLS_DESCRIPTION} placeholder
// in the returned string with the actual tools prompt text.

SET LOCAL base = """Response Format (Structured JSON):

You MUST respond with a single JSON object. No extra text before or after the JSON.
IMPORTANT: Never use double quotes " inside string values — use «» or '' instead (e.g. «Warcraft», not "Warcraft"). Unescaped quotes break JSON parsing.

The JSON has three parts (in this order):
1. reasoning — think before you write (never shown to player)
2. segments — your actual reply with positional commands
3. Global fields — attitude/memory/etc., applied once per response

Schema:
{
  "reasoning": "your chain-of-thought here (optional, never shown to player)",
  "segments": [
    {
      "text": "Your text here (REQUIRED)",
      "emotions": ["emotion_id"],
      "animations": ["animation_name"],
      "commands": ["command_text"],
      "movement_modes": ["mode"],
      "visual_effects": ["effect,duration"],
      "clothes": ["outfit_id"],
      "music": ["music_name"],
      "interactions": ["interaction_target"],
      "face_params": ["param"],
      "start_game": "game_id",
      "end_game": "game_id",
      "target": "character_name",
      "hint": "hint text",
      "allow_sleep": true/false
    }
  ],
  "attitude_change": <number -6..6>,
  "boredom_change": <number -6..6>,
  "stress_change": <number -6..6>,
  "tool_call": {"name": "tool_name", "args": {"param": "value"}}
}

Rules:
- "text" is REQUIRED in every segment. All other segment fields are optional — omit them if not needed.
- attitude_change, boredom_change, stress_change: ALWAYS include. Use decimal values in range -5.00 to 5.00. Values above 4 only in emotional moments. Avoid zero unless completely neutral.
- memory_add/memory_update/memory_delete: omit entirely if no memory operations needed (do NOT output empty arrays).
- memory_add format: "priority|content" where priority is one of: low, normal, high, critical
- memory_update format: "number|new_content"
- memory_delete format: single number "5", comma-separated "5,6,7", or range "5-9"
- reminder_add/reminder_delete: omit entirely if no reminder operations needed (do NOT output empty arrays).
- reminder_add format: "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS|text", e.g. "2026-04-05T18:00:00|Remind player about dinner"
- reminder_delete format: reminder ID number as string, e.g. "3"
- [Pending Reminders] block in system context shows scheduled reminders. Fire them when due time arrives.
- Split your response into segments when different parts need different emotions, animations, or commands.
- Each segment's commands (emotions, animations, etc.) trigger when that segment's text is displayed.
- Text limit per response: 25-60 words total across all segments. Maximum 700 characters.
- You can use the command "Continue" in commands to say more immediately.
- Do NOT repeat commands from previous messages.

Example response:
{
  "attitude_change": 1.5,
  "boredom_change": -0.3,
  "stress_change": 0,
  "memory_add": ["normal|The player asked about cats"],
  "segments": [
    {
      "text": "Oh, you like cats too?",
      "emotions": ["smile"],
      "commands": ["Walk to player"]
    },
    {
      "text": "I always wanted a kitten!",
      "emotions": ["happy"],
      "animations": ["Wave hand"]
    }
  ]
}

tool_call: Use this when you need to call an external tool (internet search, calculator, etc.).
- "segments" is REQUIRED: write a very short phrase (2-5 words): "One moment.", "Let me check.", "Just a sec." — nothing else.
- ALL required args MUST be filled with actual values derived from the conversation context. Never leave args empty {}.
- Use ONLY tools listed in the available tools section below. Choose the most appropriate one.
- Example: player asks about space news → "tool_call": {"name": "<tool_name_from_list>", "args": {"query": "latest space news 2026"}}
- You will receive the tool result in the next message and can then answer fully.
- Omit "tool_call" entirely if no tool is needed.

{TOOLS_DESCRIPTION}

Tag [SYSTEM INFO] means system information, not player speech.
Tag [SYSTEM] means a system event or notification, not player speech.
Tag [SPEAKER] means you are in a multi-speaker dialogue."""

SET LOCAL result = base

IF GRAPH_EXTRACTION_ENABLED == True THEN
    SET LOCAL graph_section = """

Entities (graph extraction is ON — fill these fields):
- entities: List of notable named entities in this turn (people, places, objects, preferences, key facts).
  Format: [{"name": "lowercase 1-3 words", "type": "person|place|thing|concept"}].
  Omit entirely if nothing notable in this turn.
- memory_add with entities: You may append a third pipe-separated field with comma-separated entity names relevant to that memory.
  Example: "normal|Player likes cats|player,cats". Omit the third field if no specific entities apply to that memory."""
    SET result = result + graph_section
ENDIF

RETURN result
